Reasoning: 
1) cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel communication-efficient parallel topic modeling architecture based on power law and combines it with the online belief propagation algorithm for big topic modeling tasks. This involves machine learning techniques and algorithms. 
2) cs.IR (Information Retrieval): Topic modeling is a popular technique in information retrieval for organizing and categorizing large collections of text data. 
3) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses reducing time and space complexities of batch LDA algorithms, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
4) cs.CL (Computation and Language): Topic modeling is a natural language processing technique used for text analysis and understanding. 
5) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel architecture and algorithm for big topic modeling, which involves artificial intelligence techniques.
